description: Triangle of number of connected graphs with n nodes and k edges (n >= 2, 1 <= k <= n(n-1)/2).
references: G. A. Baker et al., High-temperature expansions for the spin-1/2 Heisenberg model, Phys. Rev., 164 (1967), 800-817.
example: 1; 0,1,1; 0,0,2,2,1,1; 0,0,0,3,5,5,4,2,1,1 [ the last batch giving the numbers of connected graphs with 4 nodes and from 1 to 10 edges ].
crossrefs: See A054924, which is the main entry for this triangle.
author: _N. J. A. Sloane_.
